1
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:10,400
THE BOOK OF MARY

2
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:36,310
What do you think?

3
00:01:37,560 --> 00:01:39,950
You'll escape routine if you're alone?

4
00:01:41,440 --> 00:01:43,350
No, that's not it.

5
00:01:44,940 --> 00:01:47,480
But I just can't stand this deal,

6
00:01:48,920 --> 00:01:52,710
putting up with anything as
long as we stay together.

7
00:01:53,240 --> 00:01:54,720
You always come back to that.

8
00:01:55,720 --> 00:01:57,120
Admit it you are

9
00:01:57,840 --> 00:02:00,280
so afraid of being abandoned,

10
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:02,640
you're fleeing into loneliness.

11
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:04,510
You should know by now.

12
00:02:06,520 --> 00:02:07,720
Since you're here

13
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:09,030
for once

14
00:02:09,340 --> 00:02:10,630
let's be serious.

15
00:02:11,230 --> 00:02:13,720
Seeing you is hardly a blessing now.

16
00:02:14,680 --> 00:02:15,690
Even for Mary.

17
00:02:15,690 --> 00:02:16,630
It's no good.

18
00:02:17,760 --> 00:02:19,280
And I’ve had it.

19
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:23,480
I can't work, I can't sleep.

20
00:02:26,710 --> 00:02:28,800
I see, if we separate you'll sleep again?

21
00:02:30,720 --> 00:02:32,520
You see how brutal you are?

22
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:35,260
You're brutal too, in your way.

23
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:40,450
You won't face up to things.

24
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:47,480
Listen Paul, you’ve cheated on
the contract from the start.

25
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:49,110
You can't brush that off.

26
00:02:49,950 --> 00:02:54,040
I think it takes constant
inventiveness to succeed.

27
00:02:55,480 --> 00:02:59,400
In your line of work,
you've lots of time for that.

28
00:03:00,390 --> 00:03:01,910
It doesn't interest you, that's all.

29
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:05,990
So we play it safe and stay together.

30
00:03:07,060 --> 00:03:08,790
What does that do for the child?

31
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:11,560
Loving's not investing.

32
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:13,350
You can save too,

33
00:03:13,460 --> 00:03:17,600
not just give, or expect
everything from one person.

34
00:03:18,920 --> 00:03:21,840
The way you've set things up,
you could talk that way.

35
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:23,950
You're never here.

36
00:03:25,050 --> 00:03:27,000
I spent much more time at home.

37
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:30,560
I put a lot in and get little back.

38
00:03:31,980 --> 00:03:33,970
We've been over this so often.

39
00:03:35,920 --> 00:03:37,560
What other way is there?

40
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:43,890
Before, you didn't work,
you took care of Mary.

41
00:03:43,890 --> 00:03:46,460
But now we're closer
to an even footing.

42
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:48,300
I don't agree.

43
00:03:49,300 --> 00:03:52,180
I'm still here for serving,
caring for things.

44
00:03:54,700 --> 00:03:57,430
That's a mother's job,
not a woman's.

45
00:03:59,420 --> 00:04:00,580
I am tired.

46
00:04:01,720 --> 00:04:04,190
Things have got to change for a while.

47
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:07,270
You're so impatient.

48
00:04:07,440 --> 00:04:08,350
May be.

49
00:04:11,390 --> 00:04:13,170
What I know now is...

50
00:04:13,330 --> 00:04:16,320
that I don't need to be dominated
to feel understood.

51
00:04:17,530 --> 00:04:19,150
I no longer need to lose.

52
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:23,040
I don't see where that gets you either.

53
00:04:25,340 --> 00:04:26,390
I don't know.

54
00:04:28,540 --> 00:04:29,910
I want to see clearly.

55
00:04:34,240 --> 00:04:36,470
I wish you understood.

56
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:38,780
Understanding's scarce.

57
00:04:41,300 --> 00:04:44,230
Truth is often deadly.
Your truths are fatal,

58
00:04:44,340 --> 00:04:45,840
So don't complain afterwards.

59
00:04:46,960 --> 00:04:51,000
I'm not complaining,
just trying to see clearly.

60
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:54,160
Why is everyone so scared...

61
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:55,550
of clarity?

62
00:04:55,960 --> 00:04:57,140
Your eyes hurt?

63
00:04:57,930 --> 00:04:59,140
No, I'm alright.

64
00:05:04,700 --> 00:05:06,950
I don't need your total sincerity.

65
00:05:08,080 --> 00:05:11,470
It's comforting,
but not interesting.

66
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:12,960
Let's not start again.

67
00:05:13,620 --> 00:05:14,980
No, let's not.

68
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:23,960
But try to understand sometimes.

69
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:26,740
For 10 years we've copied.

70
00:05:28,620 --> 00:05:30,200
Now I want to invent.

71
00:05:30,570 --> 00:05:32,610
No one's stopped you.

72
00:05:34,130 --> 00:05:36,230
Anyway, women don't invent much.

73
00:05:36,710 --> 00:05:39,750
Even the soul was invented by a man.

74
00:05:42,060 --> 00:05:43,920
You're really encouraging.

75
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:47,270
You don't need encouragement now.

76
00:05:47,440 --> 00:05:49,830
We can see how well you
do on your own.

77
00:05:50,350 --> 00:05:53,500
Good morning! We continue
with our operation.

78
00:05:53,760 --> 00:05:56,630
Now we cut the eye in half.

79
00:05:57,010 --> 00:06:00,630
It's black, if you can see that.

80
00:06:01,100 --> 00:06:03,520
I put this inside, it's the pupil.

81
00:06:03,990 --> 00:06:08,840
The pupil, seen from outside,
magnified, of course,

82
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:10,040
is brown.

83
00:06:11,070 --> 00:06:12,910
The eye is enormous,

84
00:06:13,400 --> 00:06:16,010
but the pupil takes up a lot of space.

85
00:06:16,740 --> 00:06:19,320
The rest is water.

86
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:20,920
Water, yes.

87
00:06:21,080 --> 00:06:24,440
The pupil floats like a baby
in the belly of its mother.

88
00:06:25,030 --> 00:06:28,160
When you look at things,
it's because of the pupil,

89
00:06:28,320 --> 00:06:29,600
because it floats,

90
00:06:29,760 --> 00:06:31,070
and when we move

91
00:06:31,080 --> 00:06:33,430
as you see, it shifts.

92
00:06:33,580 --> 00:06:35,160
Understand what I’m saying?

93
00:06:35,440 --> 00:06:37,400
It's complicated, a bit technical.

94
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:40,550
Yes, it's mechanical and technical

95
00:06:40,550 --> 00:06:42,820
and at the same time surgical.

96
00:06:43,760 --> 00:06:47,200
You operate once for this illness.

97
00:06:47,750 --> 00:06:51,530
If you do it twice, the patient dies.

98
00:06:51,900 --> 00:06:53,580
In any case the eye withers.

99
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:58,080
It's a very serious operation.

100
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:01,560
Yes, I entirely agree there.

101
00:07:02,080 --> 00:07:06,760
You undergo it after you've
almost been sick.

102
00:07:07,270 --> 00:07:11,210
Because this gentleman,
you see his eye,

103
00:07:11,940 --> 00:07:15,880
has been completely... shaken, see?

104
00:07:16,480 --> 00:07:17,880
It's had a shock.

105
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:21,470
The eye's been completely terrorized,

106
00:07:22,440 --> 00:07:23,750
so...

107
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:27,670
we can't do much for it.

108
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:30,270
Well, that's all for this program.

109
00:07:31,250 --> 00:07:32,140
Good bye.

110
00:07:41,170 --> 00:07:42,430
Spoken to Mary?

111
00:07:43,790 --> 00:07:44,950
Not yet,

112
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:47,920
but I'll speak to her, of course.

113
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:53,080
And you'll have to tell her
what keeps you so far from her,

114
00:07:53,550 --> 00:07:54,390
and from me.

115
00:07:57,120 --> 00:08:00,800
You've thought of what
it'll mean to her,

116
00:08:02,520 --> 00:08:04,720
shuttling between parents?

117
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:09,630
Stop talking as if it
was all my doing.

118
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:17,280
Silence, please.

119
00:08:19,530 --> 00:08:22,230
My spirit with a heavy
fear forebodes

120
00:08:22,670 --> 00:08:25,350
In black battalions,
stray ghosts ride

121
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:28,500
Driving me on to moving roads

122
00:08:28,710 --> 00:08:31,540
closed in by bloodied
skies on every side.

123
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:35,420
How strange and wicked was our act?

124
00:08:37,050 --> 00:08:40,270
Can you explain my trouble
and my fright?

125
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:43,640
Silence!

126
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:45,950
I said, silence!

127
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:48,920
Who can tell me...

128
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:51,430
what Baudelaire meant
to express in this poem?

129
00:08:52,880 --> 00:08:55,110
If you weren't asleep, that is.

130
00:08:57,640 --> 00:09:01,080
Get out your notebooks,
I'll give you some dictation.

131
00:09:01,760 --> 00:09:05,280
Hurry! We have other things to do.

132
00:09:07,160 --> 00:09:12,150
My spirit with a heavy fear forebodes...

133
00:09:13,890 --> 00:09:16,090
Heavy fear,

134
00:09:17,350 --> 00:09:18,980
black battalions,

135
00:09:19,340 --> 00:09:20,650
with two "t's",

136
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:22,540
and stray ghosts...

137
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:26,950
Silence!

138
00:09:28,160 --> 00:09:28,950
Yes?

139
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:34,110
Mary, I have something to tell you.

140
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:35,670
All right.

141
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:40,120
Go on. And make sure you've
made no spelling errors.

142
00:09:40,330 --> 00:09:42,480
I have to talk to the principal.

143
00:09:43,160 --> 00:09:44,990
I'm sure you know what it is.

144
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:49,320
Dad's going to live elsewhere.
Not for a long time.

145
00:09:52,280 --> 00:09:54,080
Until winter, for example.

146
00:09:54,180 --> 00:09:56,550
Right. To continue:

147
00:09:57,070 --> 00:10:00,170
that seek to lead me
on shifting ways...

148
00:10:00,270 --> 00:10:01,270
Mary!

149
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:09,160
You'll see dad on weekends and holidays.

150
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:11,360
Anyway, it's not for long.

151
00:10:12,080 --> 00:10:14,540
Have we committed a strange act?
Explain if...

152
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:19,470
It's not that we don't love
each other anymore.

153
00:10:20,210 --> 00:10:21,420
On the contrary.

154
00:10:22,050 --> 00:10:24,410
But if he stays here we'll quarrel.

155
00:10:27,870 --> 00:10:31,600
There's no cause to worry.
I'd tell you if there were.

156
00:10:32,070 --> 00:10:35,320
Believe me, you can trust me.

157
00:10:39,730 --> 00:10:41,880
Why don't you want us to go to Capri?

158
00:10:44,980 --> 00:10:46,580
Because you're an ass.

159
00:10:54,950 --> 00:10:56,480
You scare me, Paul.

160
00:10:58,800 --> 00:11:01,270
- I've arrived earlier than I predicted.
- Do you need help?

161
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:03,180
Don't just stand there, answer me!

162
00:11:03,220 --> 00:11:04,810
No, not necessary.

163
00:11:05,390 --> 00:11:07,800
I'll just take two or three things.
Won't be long.

164
00:11:24,280 --> 00:11:25,800
I'm in a hurry, Mary.

165
00:11:31,990 --> 00:11:33,880
You go to Capri, Paul.

166
00:11:34,140 --> 00:11:36,080
See you Saturday, OK?

167
00:12:16,910 --> 00:12:18,010
Tell me...

168
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:20,800
about when I was little.

169
00:12:21,840 --> 00:12:23,150
Again!

170
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:24,040
Go ahead.

171
00:12:25,510 --> 00:12:28,290
You seem especially fond of hearing that.

172
00:12:30,340 --> 00:12:31,600
You're right.

173
00:12:32,810 --> 00:12:34,690
It's the strongest memory of love.

174
00:12:41,150 --> 00:12:43,670
It's hard to recover that strength

175
00:12:46,080 --> 00:12:47,550
without going backward.

176
00:12:54,950 --> 00:12:56,160
It is thus.

177
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:05,080
You just have to be able
to give and accept.

178
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:10,600
I'll prepare something to eat.
See you downstairs.

179
00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:16,960
Dry your hair well.

180
00:13:43,380 --> 00:13:44,380
Mary!

181
00:13:45,110 --> 00:13:47,160
Hello.

182
00:13:48,570 --> 00:13:49,630
What's up?

183
00:13:49,730 --> 00:13:50,870
I'm taking a train.

184
00:13:51,300 --> 00:13:52,480
Where are you going?

185
00:13:52,560 --> 00:13:54,140
To see my father.

186
00:13:54,710 --> 00:13:56,240
Doesn't he live here?

187
00:13:56,500 --> 00:13:57,710
Not right now.

188
00:13:57,880 --> 00:14:00,680
- Your folks divorced?
- No, they're not.

189
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:02,740
- Is it your bear?
- Yes.

190
00:14:03,320 --> 00:14:04,470
In any case...

191
00:14:04,640 --> 00:14:07,030
I am glad my parents are not divorced.

192
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:08,160
You have no luck.

193
00:14:08,520 --> 00:14:10,080
That's enough.

194
00:14:34,120 --> 00:14:35,060
Hello, Mimi.

195
00:14:35,590 --> 00:14:37,680
My name's not Mimi, it's Mary.

196
00:14:37,790 --> 00:14:38,740
Where you going, Mimi?

197
00:14:40,700 --> 00:14:41,610
To see my father.

198
00:14:41,730 --> 00:14:43,880
That's right, he's gone away.

199
00:14:43,900 --> 00:14:45,980
It's good for him, a little...

200
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:47,240
It's no big deal.

201
00:14:47,400 --> 00:14:48,770
Of course not.

202
00:14:48,940 --> 00:14:52,490
and you can travel with your bear,
so it's no trouble.

203
00:14:52,590 --> 00:14:54,890
It's not a bear, it's a panther.

204
00:14:54,950 --> 00:14:56,020
Certainly, you're right.

205
00:14:56,180 --> 00:15:00,620
I'm a dumbbell about animals,
I don't know.

206
00:15:00,780 --> 00:15:02,060
And where do you go?

207
00:15:02,220 --> 00:15:06,080
Passing the time. I'm on relief.

208
00:15:06,180 --> 00:15:08,800
I'm not working these days.

209
00:15:09,180 --> 00:15:12,460
I stay at home.
I have a lot of housework,

210
00:15:12,620 --> 00:15:15,890
I like my place to be clean,
you see.

211
00:15:15,940 --> 00:15:18,980
- Get bored?
- Not at all, because...

212
00:15:19,090 --> 00:15:22,390
I study my own case.

213
00:15:22,420 --> 00:15:25,600
And I have my afternoons programmed.
I go out...

214
00:15:25,750 --> 00:15:30,420
on my bike, my moped,
whatever you want to call it.

215
00:15:30,470 --> 00:15:32,100
It takes me everywhere.

216
00:15:32,460 --> 00:15:35,180
I get back at 7 or 9 in the evening.

217
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:38,140
If the weather is good, I take my time,

218
00:15:38,190 --> 00:15:39,850
I stop where I please.

219
00:15:45,580 --> 00:15:49,130
Forever damned be
the feckless dreamer

220
00:15:49,980 --> 00:15:53,040
who, in his stupidity, first strove,

221
00:15:53,380 --> 00:15:56,870
enamored of an insoluble
and sterile problem

222
00:15:57,300 --> 00:16:00,580
to mix honesty with love.

223
00:16:38,380 --> 00:16:40,580
Have you studied triangles?

224
00:16:40,740 --> 00:16:42,620
We've just started.

225
00:16:43,250 --> 00:16:45,410
I have to know the 4 types for Monday.

226
00:16:48,860 --> 00:16:50,740
Know what a jagged line is?

227
00:16:51,860 --> 00:16:54,220
One that changes direction.

228
00:16:55,060 --> 00:16:56,160
Yes, but how?

229
00:16:58,100 --> 00:16:59,380
By forming angles.

230
00:17:00,140 --> 00:17:01,260
And an angle?

231
00:17:01,880 --> 00:17:03,330
It's when the lines close.

232
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:05,900
And when they meet?

233
00:17:06,540 --> 00:17:07,740
That's the vertex.

234
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:12,490
Also called an intersection.

235
00:17:13,690 --> 00:17:15,310
An angle's like this.

236
00:17:16,100 --> 00:17:17,770
Yes, but also like this.

237
00:17:18,140 --> 00:17:19,890
No, it's like this.

238
00:17:21,030 --> 00:17:23,100
To get that, you first need this.

239
00:17:25,860 --> 00:17:26,800
All right.

240
00:17:26,980 --> 00:17:30,940
There are 4 kinds of triangles.

241
00:17:32,680 --> 00:17:34,520
The right-angle triangle,

242
00:17:35,420 --> 00:17:36,980
It looks like this.

243
00:17:38,090 --> 00:17:42,210
The side opposite the right angle
is the hypotenuse.

244
00:17:44,380 --> 00:17:47,260
The equilateral triangle

245
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:49,570
is the one that has three equal sides.

246
00:17:51,570 --> 00:17:53,460
The isosceles triangle

247
00:17:55,780 --> 00:17:57,060
You listening, Mary?

248
00:17:59,260 --> 00:18:01,700
The isosceles has two equal sides

249
00:18:02,430 --> 00:18:04,900
and the scalene has three unequal sides.

250
00:18:05,340 --> 00:18:08,020
Draw them, helps you
to remember them.

251
00:18:27,360 --> 00:18:28,510
Are you hungry?

252
00:18:28,720 --> 00:18:30,300
Yes, terribly.

253
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:47,300
Want a bite?

254
00:19:03,420 --> 00:19:05,620
That the concerto I liked so much?

255
00:19:05,980 --> 00:19:07,180
Yes, that's the one.

256
00:19:08,780 --> 00:19:10,010
Don't recognize it?

257
00:19:10,120 --> 00:19:10,930
Oh, yes.

258
00:19:11,140 --> 00:19:13,430
No, not really, in fact.

259
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:19,090
Sounds like talk, don't you think?

260
00:19:21,620 --> 00:19:23,290
People in a discussion.

261
00:19:27,960 --> 00:19:29,330
Agreeing or disagreeing?

262
00:19:30,430 --> 00:19:31,690
A bit of both.

263
00:19:33,260 --> 00:19:36,410
Changes of mod, icy, exasperated,

264
00:19:36,580 --> 00:19:37,650
I demand.

265
00:19:37,820 --> 00:19:41,750
fire, fire, attention, error, horror, suffering...

266
00:19:41,760 --> 00:19:42,860
Hey, calm down.

267
00:19:49,160 --> 00:19:51,630
There's a Mahler symphony I can't find.

268
00:19:52,260 --> 00:19:54,250
Ask mom for it next time.

269
00:19:54,420 --> 00:19:55,300
OK.

270
00:20:07,680 --> 00:20:09,620
Mary, bring your pajamas, too.

271
00:20:18,180 --> 00:20:19,900
and don't forget your toothbrush again.

272
00:20:29,980 --> 00:20:31,610
We've got to go now. It's time.

273
00:20:32,550 --> 00:20:33,810
You ready?

274
00:21:10,230 --> 00:21:11,070
